Package com.poesys.db.dao.delete

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDelete<T extends IDbDto>
    An interface for a Command pattern class that deletes an object in the database.
    IDeleteBatch<T extends IDbDto>
    An interface for a Command pattern class that deletes a batch of objects in the database.
    IDeleteCollection<T extends IDbDto>
    An interface for a Command pattern class that deletes a collection of objects from the database.
    IDeleteQuery
    An interface for a Command pattern class that deletes a set of objects identified by a query (a SELECT statement).
    IDeleteSql<T extends IDbDto>
    An interface that defines the set of operations required by an IDelete or IDeleteBatch object to build a SQL DELETE statement for a data transfer object (DTO).
    IDeleteSqlWithParameters<T extends IDbDto,P extends IDbDto>
    An interface that defines the set of operations required by an IDeleteWithParameters object to build a SQL DELETE statement for a data transfer object (DTO) that is parameterized by a second DTO.
    IDeleteSqlWithQuery
    An interface that defines the set of operations required by an IDeleteQuery object to build a SQL DELETE statement that has no parameters and deletes a set of objects based on a query.
    IDeleteWithParameters<T extends IDbDto,P extends IDbDto>
    An interface for a Command pattern class that deletes a set of objects based on a set of parameters contained in a data transfer object (DTO).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDeleteSql<T extends IDbDto>
    SQL statement specification for deleting a standard object.
    AbstractDeleteSqlWithQuery
    SQL statement specification for deleting objects identified by a query.
    DeleteBatchByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    An implementation of the IDeleteBatch generic interface that contains the base code for deleting a batch of objects in the database.
    DeleteByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    An implementation of the IDelete interface that updates an object, identifying the object in the database using the primary key of the data transfer object (DTO).
    DeleteByQuery  
    DeleteCacheBatchByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    A subclass of the DeleteBatchByKey class that removes the deleted data transfer object (DTO) from the cache.
    DeleteCacheByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    A subclass of the DeleteByKey class that removes the deleted data transfer object from the cache.
    DeleteCacheCollectionByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    A subclass of the DeleteCollectionByKey class that removes the deleted data transfer object (DTO) from the cache.
    DeleteCollectionByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    An implementation of the IDeleteCollection generic interface that contains the base code for deleting a collection of objects in the database.
    DeleteMemcachedBatchByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    A subclass of the DeleteBatchByKey class that removes the deleted data transfer object (DTO) from the memcached cache.
    DeleteMemcachedByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    A subclass of the DeleteByKey class that removes the deleted data transfer object from the memcached distributed cache.
    DeleteMemcachedCollectionByKey<T extends IDbDto>
    A subclass of the DeleteCollectionByKey class that removes the deleted data transfer object (DTO) from the memcached cache.
    DeleteWithParameters<T extends IDbDto,P extends IDbDto>
    An implementation of the IDeleteWithParameters interface that deletes a set of objects with a single DELETE statement parameterized with the contents of a data transfer object.
